<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1884-02-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1884-02-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="141" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d141">
                    <head>No. 141.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Lowell</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1884-02-20"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 20,
                            1884</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Ship an unconditional gift, with anchor, chains, and such of her equipment as
                        can be utilized.</p>
                    <p>Shall we accept her? We fit her out. Greens most reliable firm in London.</p>
                    <p>Please answer at once.</p>
                    <closer><signed>LOWELL,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Minister.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>